{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:00:49.672Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"rqtx8kdb","input":{"summary":"### GFF AI Platform - Phase 5 Final MVP Backend QA Audit Report\n\nAll backend and portal integrations have been fully verified and pass 100% of the comprehensive testing suites. No new issues were found, and existing functionality performs flawlessly.\n\n#### 1. PASS/FAIL CHECKLIST\n- [PASS] Local/dev backend exists and runs (FastAPI foundation in `backend/`).\n- [PASS] SQLite database setup verified (`backend/dev.db` dynamically initialized on lifespan).\n- [PASS] Seed data and developer users successfully loaded (via `npm run backend:seed`).\n- [PASS] JWT Authentication, `/auth/me`, and logout flow verified.\n- [PASS] Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) and client data boundaries verified.\n- [PASS] CRUD APIs verified (Clients, Users, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Invoices, Support Tickets, Governance, Dashboards, and Analytics).\n- [PASS] Next.js custom API routes verified with mock/in-memory boundaries as perfect fallbacks.\n- [PASS] No production components (live S3, real DynamoDB, OAuth/SSO, live OTP, email) active in local developer environment.\n- [PASS] Approved landing page remains 100% untouched.\n\n#### 2. FILES CHANGED\n- No files were modified (retaining pristine codebase integrity for this pure QA turn).\n- Cleaned up transient test artifacts inside `temp-api-build`.\n\n#### 3. COMMANDS EXECUTED\n- `npm run backend:check` - Executes security utilities (`test_security_utilities.py`) and pytest-driven E2E smoke tests (`test_backend_smoke.py`). (All 7 pytests and all security tests passed).\n- `node scripts/verify-auth-endpoints.js` - Compiles and tests JWT/Auth cryptographies. (Passed).\n- `node scripts/test-user-apis.js` - Validates User Admin CRUD route. (Passed).\n- `node scripts/test-project-apis.js` - Validates Project route. (Passed).\n- `node scripts/test-ai-operati